Topic: Styling in HTML

Language which is used to add styles to HTML tags is CSS. 
CSS mean Cascading Style Sheet.

Every tag has its own properties/attributes.
For example: <img src="image.png">
Here img is the tag name and src is the property/attribute. The text after equal sign (=) is the value of src attribute.

The style attribute can be applied on almost all of the tags.

Colon :
Semi-colon ;
